{
  "stem": "10588.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "How do you remember?' I said, 'Well, I guess God blessed me with a good memory.' Which is a blessing, and also a curse sometimes, because I remember what I had and what I lost.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So in a way, it's good.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Now, what type of religious background, upbringing did you have?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, my, my little brother started to go to Hebrew when he was only three years old, because that was required for boys in-- I started to go, I must have been about six years or so, started to go.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They had [NON-ENGLISH], they used to call it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Here, it would be called [NON-ENGLISH], you know, girl for school.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And to tell you the truth, I was a very good student in public school.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I liked when they talked about Yiddish history and everything.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But when they spoke in Hebrew, and I was kind always resisted to accept something that I couldn't understand, which I realize now was a mistake, because if I would have learned the words, later if I would get older I would learn the meaning.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But I had from the home, you know, because we observed the, all the Yiddish holidays and had the kashrut and had all the, you know, Jewish history and everything.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And so I've learned to see it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I spoke fluently Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I still do.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "At home with my husband, I only speak Yiddish, till this day and with most of my friends.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And Yiddish literature-- in fact, I have a story, which is really amazing.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "You know, we didn't have, like we have now, built-in closets, you know, like, sliding doors.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "What we had was called a French armoire.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "You know, it's like a-- it was a chest, a tall chest, that reached almost from the floor to the ceiling.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And it had two doors.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "When you faced it, this, the right-hand side was a little bit narrower, broader than the other one.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "One was usually used for the wardrobe.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And the other side, it was linen, nicely-pressed linen, and with ribbons around, and the very highest had shelf in it.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "For some reason, when I was a little girl, the door where the wardrobe was supposed to be was always locked.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And I couldn't figure out why.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "So I used to play all kinds of games.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "You know, I was a very imaginative child.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "You know, since earliest childhood, I had a wonderful imagination.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I was a curious child, and my family always encouraged that curiosity.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I used to think, guessing games-- maybe a skeleton, maybe a treasure.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I even went as far as to think maybe I was adopted.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I couldn't understand, why is it locked?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And one time, my mother said, 'Itkele, please come.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I want to show you something.' I was trembling with fear and excited with anticipation simultaneously, wondering what is in that closet here and what's so important?",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "My mother took the key, opened the closet, and there was a whole chest-- it was a closet, was that [INAUDIBLE] of the chest, full with books-- poetry books and, and other books, you know, beautiful bound books.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And my mother pointed to the books, took out the book, and she said to me, 'Itkele, when you're going to learn how to read, you're going to find a treasure here.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You can sit right here in Ciechonw.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You will travel through the world, through the ages, with the greatest mind, everything.' She made it so amazing.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the reason why she had it locked when we were very little is because I was the oldest of three children, and I was still a little girl.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So she was afraid that the little children might damage the book.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Later on, when we became older, it was open.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And when I learned to-- eagerly to read Yiddish, I was devouring the Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And she read me all kinds of stories.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But one story that really became, later, relevant to my life was the story called [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "She read it in Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It's called It was written by a Yiddish, Leib Peretz.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And briefly, I'd like to share that story, because it was very relevant later to my life.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I was thinking about it a lot during the concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It was about a boy, whose name was Bontsha, but, unfortunately, lost his mother when he was a little child.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "His father took another wife when he was 13 years old, which was a very cruel woman and constantly abused Bontsha.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "She would begrudge him the food while she ate very well.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "She would not give him clothes.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "He never had a friend.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "He was lonely.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And the coldest winter time, she would chase him out barefoot to chop wood, and all those things.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
